column19: one Niskin five times down to 2m depth
column20: sample pre-filtration 200 μm. long term monitoring station in the Rovinj coastal zone (1 nautical mile from the coast) at 1pm local time with Burin R/V-collect 20L of seawater from 2m depth using Niskin bottles-filtration start one hour after the sampling-unicellular Eukaryotes in the size-fraction > 0.8μm using peristaltic pump and polycarbontate membranes with a pore size of 0.8μm (diameter 47 mm)- do replicates and record filtration time and volume for each place filter membranes in 5 mL cryotubes and store immediately in a -80c freezer until shipping.
